        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 7:10PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northeast of Eva, or 9 miles south of Elkhart, moving northwest
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eva.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
